children.text: The eaves in this area are either sagging down, or will almost certainly do so in the future due to inadequate framing inside the boxed eave, which will eventually be at risk of falling out of the fascia and dropping if the sheets sag much further.
Part 3.5.4.5 Eaves and soffit linings of the NCC’s Building Code of Australia (BCA), requires that
‘Where provided, external fibre-cement sheets and linings used as eaves and soffit linings must be fixed in accordance with Table 3.5.4.6 and Figure 3.5.4.4’ .

These eave linings should have additional soffit bearers installed and the linings fixed to these bearers at appropriate centres to ensure that they are properly supported and are constructed in accordance with the requirements of the BCA.
